servinfo.title: DTC P0533: A/C Refrigerant Pressure Sensor Circuit High

servinfosub.title: Wiring Diagram
servinfosub.ptxt: Refer to DTC P0532: A/C Refrigerant Pressure Sensor Circuit Low:M16A and J20A .

servinfosub.title: DTC Detecting Condition and Trouble Area

entry.ptxt: A/C refrigerant pressure sensor signal voltage is higher than 4.93 V for 0.5 sec. continuously.
(1 driving detection logic but MIL does not light up)

attention3.ptxt: When DTC P0108, P0113 and P0118 are indicated together, it is possible that “GRY/GRN” wire circuit open.

s1.ptxt: Connect scan tool to DLC with ignition switch turned OFF.
Turn ON ignition switch and clear DTC using scan tool.

attention3.ptxt: Before this trouble shooting is performed, read the precautions for DTC troubleshooting referring to Precautions for DTC Troubleshooting:M16A and J20A .

testgroup.question: Was “Engine and Emission Control System Check” performed?

action.ptxt: Go to Engine and Emission Control System Check:M16A and J20A

testgroup.title: A/C refrigerant pressure sensor power supply circuit check

test1.ptxt: Disconnect connector from A/C refrigerant pressure sensor with ignition switch turned OFF.
Check for proper connection of A/C refrigerant pressure sensor at “GRY/RED”, “GRY/BLK” and “GRY/GRN” wire terminals.
Turn ON ignition switch, measure voltage between engine ground and “GRY/RED” wire terminal of A/C refrigerant pressure sensor connector.

testgroup.question: Is voltage 4 – 6 V?

testgroup.title: A/C refrigerant pressure sensor signal circuit check

test1.ptxt: Turn ON ignition switch, measure voltage between engine ground and “GRY/BLK” wire terminal of A/C refrigerant pressure sensor connector.

testgroup.question: Is voltage 4 – 6 V?

testgroup.title: A/C refrigerant pressure sensor signal circuit check

test1.ptxt: Disconnect connectors from ECM with ignition switch turned OFF.
Measure resistance between “GRY/BLK” wire terminal of A/C refrigerant pressure sensor connector and “C37-12” terminal of ECM connector.

testgroup.question: Is resistance below 2 Ω?

action.ptxt: “GRY/BLK” wire is shorted to power supply circuit.
“GRY/BLK” wire is open or high resistance circuit.

testgroup.title: A/C refrigerant pressure sensor ground circuit check

test1.ptxt: Turn OFF ignition switch, measure resistance between engine ground and “GRY/GRN” wire terminal of A/C refrigerant pressure sensor connector.

testgroup.question: Is resistance below 5 Ω?

test1.ptxt: Remove ECM from its bracket with ECM connectors connected.
Measure resistance between engine ground and “C37-57” terminal of ECM connector.

action.ptxt: “GRY/GRN” wire is open or high resistance circuit.
ECM grounds “C37-58”, “C37-48”, “C37-30”, “C37-29” and/or “C37-15” is open or high resistance circuit.

test1.ptxt: Check A/C refrigerant pressure sensor referring to A/C Refrigerant Pressure Sensor and Its Circuit Inspection (Petrol Engine Model):M16A, J20A and F9Q Model

action.ptxt: Substitute a known-good ECM and recheck.
